    "revise": "You are the FIGURE REVISER (Opus) for \"The LLM Stack\". Chapter: content/06-rl-infra/11-scaling-rl-tricks.md\nThe chapter's core intuitions: The bubble is the whole game: heavy-tailed generation lengths mean most workers finish early and idle while one long trace gates the step; efficiency is captured by the single number eta_gen = mean(L)/max(L), which one 8x outlier can crush to ~0.12.; Oversubscription + continuous batching + a shared pull-queue attack that bubble by refilling freed slots from a deep queue, so only the final tail remains idle; overlapping generation with training (1-step off-policy) is the largest single win.; Partial rollout treats a truncated long trace as a checkpoint, amortizing it across steps, but the resumed prefix is off-policy and must be importance-corrected per token.; Group-relative advantage is exactly zero when all G rewards in a group are equal, so all-correct (easy) and all-wrong (hard) prompts cost G generations and yield no gradient; DAPO filters these and oversamples to a full useful batch, and this is only cheap on an async, oversubscribed generation layer.\n\nReview each of these figures (the ones this chapter just drew/edited):\n  scalingrl-gen-bubble-oversubscribe, scalingrl-dynamic-sampling-zero-gradient, scalingrl-sync-step-phases, scalingrl-overlap-pipeline\n\nFor EACH: render and SEE it \u2014 `python3 scripts/preview_fig.py <NAME> --theme both` from /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook,\nthen view /tmp/figpreview/<NAME>.light.png and .dark.png. Judge strictly:\n  - Does it actually BUILD INTUITION for its concept (not just decorate)? Is it correct vs the chapter?\n  - Theme-safe (no hardcoded primary color; readable in BOTH light and dark)?\n  - Nothing clipped by the viewBox; no illegible overlaps; no tofu glyphs (ASCII only in the SVG)?\n  - Marker present in the chapter exactly once; figcaption has a bold lead + takeaway?\nIf a figure has ANY problem, FIX it: Edit /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook/figures/<NAME>.html (and re-render to confirm), or\nfix a missing/duplicate marker in the chapter. Re-verify after fixing.\n\nSet verdict per figure: good / fixed / still-broken / missing. `passed` = every figure good-or-fixed\nAND present. Return the structured object."
